WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.000
[Screen recording: VulnRap landing page loads]

00:04.000 --> 00:09.000
The submission form accepts a vulnerability report title and description.

00:09.000 --> 00:14.000
[User types a report title into the input field]

00:14.000 --> 00:20.000
A detailed description of the vulnerability is entered, including reproduction steps.

00:20.000 --> 00:26.000
[User clicks the Analyze button]

00:26.000 --> 00:33.000
VulnRap scores the report across multiple dimensions: substance, linguistics, and CWE classification.

00:33.000 --> 00:40.000
[Score breakdown panel appears showing AVRI composite score]

00:40.000 --> 00:47.000
The AVRI composite score summarises overall report quality. Higher scores indicate clearer, more actionable reports.

00:47.000 --> 00:54.000
[Triage recommendation badge appears]

00:54.000 --> 01:01.000
A triage recommendation — Accept, Review, or Reject — is surfaced alongside the score breakdown.

01:01.000 --> 01:08.000
[Redaction panel expands]

01:08.000 --> 01:15.000
Sensitive tokens are automatically detected and replaced with [REDACTED] before the report is stored or shared.

01:15.000 --> 01:22.000
[Report comparison view opens with two side-by-side panels]

01:22.000 --> 01:29.000
Two reports can be compared side by side to evaluate relative quality and completeness.

01:29.000 --> 01:35.000
[Screen returns to the landing page]

01:35.000 --> 01:40.000
VulnRap — automated vulnerability report triage.
